OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F406A1779228661
OL,3,CWaltham Forest teachers striking over
OL,4,Cpay and school funding
OL,6,FA Department for Education
OL,7,Fspokesperson said: "Our recent
OL,8,Fproposals mean teacher pay would rise
OL,9,Fby almost 17% across this parliament,
OL,10,Fequating to a significant real terms
OL,11,Fincrease over the five years. Despite
OL,12,Fdeeply challenging choices about
OL,13,Fpublic spending, mainstream school
OL,14,Ffunding will rise again next year,
OL,15,Freaching almost #51 billion, to help
OL,16,Fevery child to achieve and thrive."
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
